<p>"<b>Harrison Bergeron</b>" is a <a href="/wiki/Dystopia" title="Dystopia">dystopian</a> <a href="/wiki/Science_fiction" title="Science fiction">science fiction</a> <a href="/wiki/Short_story" title="Short story">short story</a> written by <a href="/wiki/Kurt_Vonnegut,_Jr." title="Kurt Vonnegut, Jr." class="mw-redirect">Kurt Vonnegut, Jr.</a> and first published in October, 1961. Throughout the story Vonnegut uses satire, and the story itself could be classified as a satire. Originally published in <i><a href="/wiki/The_Magazine_of_Fantasy_and_Science_Fiction" title="The Magazine of Fantasy and Science Fiction" class="mw-redirect">The Magazine of Fantasy and Science Fiction</a></i>, the story was re-published in the author's collection, <i><a href="/wiki/Welcome_to_the_Monkey_House" title="Welcome to the Monkey House">Welcome to the Monkey House</a></i> in 1968.</p>
